{
  "text": "Hypovolemia impairs sweating [CITATION_1] , but decreased preload can cause more than reflex bradycardia as demonstrated by progressive vagal symptoms including sweating, nausea and syncope [CITATION_2] . Conversely, hypervolemia does not contribute to sweating [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
